observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the BAC to:
observe strictly the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 and GPPB Circular No. 01-2020 dated April 6, 2020 to ensure adherence to the principles of transparency, competitiveness and public monitoring;
prepare and submit the required documents/reports cited in the above observations and ensure that each procurement are duly supported with complete documentation;
furnish the Audit Team with a copy of the Contract Agreement/Purchase Order and its attachments within five working days from execution/issuance thereof as required under Sections 3.1.1 and 3.2.1 of COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 23, 2009; and
in lieu of submission of Acceptance and Inspection Report (AIR) to the Audit Team, require the attachment of detailed pictures of the delivered items to be attached as proof of delivery.

We further recommended that the Municipal Accountant see to it that all the necessary documentary requirements attached to the vouchers are accurate and complete before processing the claims. Likewise ensure that POs and contracts were duly stamped and received by the Audit Team to facilitate the timely review and promptly inform the management of the defects and/or deficiencies noted.

We recommended that the:
Municipal Accountant reconcile their records with GSIS, Pag-IBIG and PhilHealth and make the necessary adjustments, if warranted;
Municipal Treasurer ensure that the contributions are remitted within the prescribed period to avoid payment of penalties;
Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer identify the employees whose GSIS, Pag-IBIG and PhilHealth contributions or loan amortizations were still not yet remitted and effect the immediate remittance thereof; and
Municipal Treasurer, thru the AAO, report to GSIS the updated list of all of its employees, their corresponding employment status, positions, salaries and such other pertinent information, including subsequent changes therein, if any, as required under Section 6.a of the IRR of R.A. No. 8291.
